name: acetyl-CoA carboxylase
classes: Ligases that form carbon-carbon bonds (only sub-subclass identified to date)
reaction: ATP + acetyl-CoA + HCO3- = ADP + phosphate + malonyl-CoA [RN:R00742]
comment: A biotinyl-protein. Also catalyses transcarboxylation; the plant enzyme also carboxylates propanonyl-CoA and butanoyl-CoA.

orthologs.K01962: acetyl-CoA carboxylase carboxyl transferase subunit alpha
orthologs.K01963: acetyl-CoA carboxylase carboxyl transferase subunit beta
orthologs.K11263: acetyl-CoA/propionyl-CoA carboxylase, biotin carboxylase, biotin carboxyl carrier protein

references.title: Fat metabolism in higher plants. XVI. Acetyl coenzyme A carboxylase and acyl coenzyme A-malonyl coenzyme A transcarboxylase from wheat germ.
[ON THE BIOSYNTHESIS OF FATTY ACIDS. V. ACETYL-COA CARBOXYLASE FROM RAT LIVER AND ITS ACTIVATION BY CITRIC ACID.]
[ON THE BIOSYNTHESIS OF FATTY ACIDS. IV. ACETYL-COA CARBOXYLASE FROM YEAST.]
A malonic acid derivative as an intermediate in fatty acid synthesis.
